thesis...



On 10/04/2006, at 1:21 PM, Adam Wright wrote:

> Now that sounds an awful lot like what I'm planning (was planning?)
> on doing with my year :)
>
> No chance of an abstract, at least, I suppose? I've only recently
> finished my proposal so if I'm planning on covering too much of the
> same territory you've been exploring I'd quite like to know.
>
>
> On 09/04/2006, at 5:14 AM, Bryan Adams wrote:
>
>> I also think it sounds like a good idea.  In fact, it sounds somewhat
>> similar to something I've implemented for my PhD thesis.  Great minds
>> think alike!  I'd say more, but I'm about 30 days away from my
>> defense,
>> so I'm at full capacity collecting data and writing.
>>
>> (There are enough differences, btw, that you should definitely keep
>> going.  My stuff is intended for use on robots, I'm less  
>> interested in
>> symmetry and more in repeated structure, I'm not using bilateral
>> symmetry, etc.  So no worries on that front.)
>>
>> I'll post my thesis to this list when it's done.
>>
>> --Bryan
